('Modellistica termica elettrica e di invecchiamento di batterie per veicoli elettrici', 47, 'bonfitto.angelo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['BATTERIA AGLI IONI DI LITIO','MODELLAZIONE MULTIFISICA','PROVE SPERIMENTALI']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['17 - Progettazione Di Macchine Rotanti E Sistemi Meccatronici']::text[], 'L''attività è dedicata alla caratterizzazione sperimentale e allo sviluppo di modelli termici, elettrici e di invecchiamento di celle di batterie agli ioni di litio per applicazioni veicolari.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-04-11', 1, ARRAY['L-35 - Mathematical Sciences','L-42 - History']::text[]),
('Natural Language Processing based Automatic Ingestion of Automotive Data', 333, 'garza.paolo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['Torino']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-04 - Database And Data Mining Group - Dbdm']::text[], 'JATO is a market-leading company in business intelligence in the automotive sector, with operations in dozens of overseas markets. JATO headquarters are based in London, UK; a local business unit is present in Torino.
 In the past 40 years, JATO has been a leader in the research and acquisition of automotive data. More recently, the company has been enhancing its capability of acquiring data by employing machine learning techniques and automation. 
 The objective of this thesis is to apply transformer models/large language models to map entities in input data streams to the JATO lexicon and to validate the results. The thesis will be carried out within the Data Science function in JATO, with mentorship from an experienced data scientist.', ARRAY['Essential pre-requisites are a basic knowledge of machine learning techniques and python, good problem solving and programming skills, and an average grade of 27/30 or over and a good level of English. Knowledge of NLP methodologies is a plus.']::text[], '', '2023-12-31', 1, ARRAY['L-39 - Social Work','L-13 - Biological Sciences']::text[]),
('Verifica di Sicurezza nei dispositivi IoT', 185, 'valenza.fulvio@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Alessandra Rizzardi (Uninsubria)']::text[], ARRAY['CYBERSECURITY','IOT PROTOCOLS','MQTT']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-03 - Computer Networks Group - Netgroup']::text[], 'Definizione ed implementazione di un sistema per il monitoraggio del comportamento di sicurezza di dispositivi IoT (Internet of Things) in comunicazione tramite protocollo MQTT (Message Queue Telemetry Transport). Tali dispositivi espongono specifiche policy relative alla condivisione delle informazioni, la cui applicazione deve essere verificata dal sistema.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-02-21', 2, ARRAY['LM-06 - Master Degree in Biology']::text[]),
('Secure Enclave for private ML IP execution', 99, 'patti.edoardo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Luca Barbierato(Luca.Barbierato@tmtest.polito.it)']::text[], ARRAY['DISTRIBUTED SYSTEM','INTERNET OF THINGS','IOT']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Eda Group','Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Ict4Ss - Ict For Smart Societies']::text[], 'Secure Enclave is a hardware-based security technology that provides a trusted execution environment (TEE) for executing sensitive code and data. It is often used to protect private ML IPs, such as ML models and algorithms, from unauthorised access and tampering.
Secure Enclave is typically implemented as a dedicated hardware module within a CPU or SoC (System-on-Chip). This module has its own memory and processing resources and is isolated from the rest of the system by a hardware security boundary. This makes it very difficult for attackers to access or modify the code and data that is being executed within the Secure Enclave.
 There are a number of benefits to using Secure Enclave for private ML IP execution:
- **Confidentiality:** Secure Enclave can protect the confidentiality of private ML IPs by encrypting them at rest and in transit. This prevents unauthorised users from accessing the ML IP, even if they can compromise the rest of the system.
- **Integrity:** Secure Enclave can protect the integrity of private ML IPs by ensuring that it is not modified without authorisation. This is done by using digital signatures to verify the authenticity of the ML IP before it is executed.
- **Attestation:** Secure Enclave can be used to attest to the authenticity of private ML IPs. This can be useful for proving to third parties that the ML IP is genuine and has not been tampered with.
 Here are some examples of how Secure Enclave is being used to protect private ML IP in the real world:
- **Google Pixel phones:** Google uses Secure Enclave to protect the Face Unlock feature on Pixel phones. The facial recognition model is stored and executed within the Secure Enclave, which prevents it from being accessed by unauthorised apps.
- **Apple iPhone:** Apple uses Secure Enclave to protect various sensitive data on the iPhone, including the user''s fingerprint and facial recognition data and the data used by Apple Pay.
- **Qualcomm Snapdragon SoCs:** Qualcomm integrates Secure Enclave into its Snapdragon SoCs, which are used in a wide range of devices, including smartphones, tablets, and wearables. This allows developers to use Secure Enclave to protect their ML IP on Qualcomm-powered devices.
 The main objective of the thesis is to develop a Secure Enclave system for private Machine Learning Intellectual Property (ML IP) execution within a System-on-Chip (SoC) designed at the University of Bologna. Specifically, it involves a GAP8 core developed by GreenWave Technology featuring a cluster of 8 RISC-V cores capable of accelerating the execution of specific deep-learning model kernels.
 Currently, the system is programmed using DORY, a toolchain that compiles a neural network and accelerates its execution on the cluster. The thesis aims to enhance DORY by integrating steps for decoding and verifying the deep learning model, assuming that the cluster resides within a Secure Enclave.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-11-03', 1, ARRAY['L-38 - Zootechnical Sciences and Animal Production Technologies','L-16 - Administration and Organization Sciences','L-28 - Navigation Sciences and Technologies']::text[]),
('Analisi della siccità in Piemonte', 343, 'revelli.roberto@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['viglione.alberto@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['Analisi della siccità']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['LM-29 group 2','LM-03 group 1']::text[], 'Analisi della siccità in Piemonte', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-03-02', 2, ARRAY['LM-29 - Master Degree in Electronic Engineering','LM-03 - Master Degree in Landscape Architecture']::text[]),
('Cyber-sickness mitigation techniques in virtual scenarios', 91, 'lamberti.fabrizio@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['REALTA'' VIRTUALE E AUMENTATA']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Gr-09 - Graphics And Intelligent Systems - Grains']::text[], 'Cyber-sickness is a disorder characterized by symptoms like nausea or discomfort, that can happen meanwhile or after using Virtual Reality (VR) technologies. Similarly to motion sickness, it is mainly caused by inconsistency between visual and aural stimuli from the simulated virtual environment and the expected feedback from the vestibular system. Several mitigation and prevention techniques have been proposed and adopted in many commercial products. However, most of them are highly situational, or require implementation choices that have a negative impact on core aspects such immersion, naturalness, and sense of presence.
 In order to support a comprehensive evaluation and fair comparison of such techniques, a testbed including a set of four immersive scenarios able to stimulate different, controlled levels of cyber-sickness has been developed in a previous thesis.
 The aim of this new thesis will be to study the state-of-the-art of cyber-sickness mitigation and prevention techniques by implementing them in the above testbed, and to possibly design new and more effective strategies for addressing this major issue of immersive Virtual Reality.

