('Design and development of the switching resonator for wirelessly powered implants', 444, 'demarchi.danilo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['mottoros.paolo@tmtest.polito.it','Gian Luca Barbruni (Gianluca.Barbruni@Epfl.Ch)']::text[], ARRAY['IMPLANTABLE MEDICAL DEVICES (IMD)','INDUTIVE LINK','NEURAL INTERFACE','WIRELESS POWER TRANSFER (WPT)']::text[], 'DESIGN AND EXPERIMENTS', ARRAY['Mines (Micro&Nano Electronic Systems — Https://Mines.Polito.It)']::text[], 'Next generation implants will be miniaturised and wirelessly powered. The standard architecture to inductively power a biomedical implant is based on an external transmitter coil and an implanted receiver coil resonating at the same operating frequency.
