('Digital Twins in the Aviation Sector: Assessing the Gap Between Theory and Reality', 48, 'davidelorenzodallavedova.matteo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['maggiore.paolo@tmtest.polito.it','Leonardo Baldo']::text[], ARRAY['AEROSPACE','COMPUTATIONAL MODELING','COMPUTATIONAL TOPOLOGY','ALGORITHMS DEVELOPMENT','DIGITAL TWIN','REVIEW']::text[], 'REVIEW, REVIEW OF ARTICLES', ARRAY['16-Astra: Additive Manufacturing For Systems And Structures In Aerospace']::text[], 'Digital twins (DTs) are virtual replicas of real-world objects or systems that span their lifecycle, are updated from real-time data, and use simulation, machine learning, and reasoning to aid decision-making. They are highly complex virtual models that accurately represent physical entities. The market for digital twins is expected to grow significantly across various industries. While digital twins have already made substantial progress in several sectors, there is still room for further advancements. On top of that, there is much confusion about what a DT is and what is not. Nevertheless, there is a lot of work still left to do and a systematic review which assesses the state-of-the-art and how far we have gone could be beneficial for both the academia and the industries.', ARRAY['Basic understanding of aerospace systems']::text[], 'Interest in the aerospace world and computational topics', '2024-10-31', 2, ARRAY['LM-23 - Master Degree in Civil Engineering']::text[]),
('Neural networks for optimization: a quantum computing application', 380, 'montrucchio.bartolomeo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['interaction pattern',' of ','
The ']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['L-40 group 1']::text[], 'This thesis settles in the context of a quantum computing application but does not require a deep knowledge of the underlying physics.
Among the currently available quantum architectures, the candidate will address neutral atoms quantum machines, such as Pasqal and QuEra technologies. These quantum architectures rely on Rydberg atoms that are positioned onto a 2D/3D register and interact, defining a unit-disk graph. To map computational problems of interest (e.g., combinatorial optimization problems) on these quantum machines, it is required to find the positions of the atoms and retrieve the interaction pattern of interest, still compliant with hardware constraints. Solving this embedding problem is equivalent to solving a constrained unit-disk graph problem (NP-hard) and requires the implementation of custom heuristics to scale with an increasing number of atoms.
In this regard, machine learning can come in handy, so the candidates will work on neural networks’ development to solve the embedding problem.
The pre-requirements to successfully address this thesis are knowledge about optimization, machine learning and sound Python or Julia programming skills.
The duration of the thesis work is expected to be around  6 months, adjustable based on the specific needs and skills.
Send CV to chiara.vercellino@linksfoundation.com and giacomo.vitali@linksfoundation.com specifying the thesis title.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2023-12-19', 1, ARRAY['L-40 - Sociology']::text[]),
('Thesis in Leonardo Labs', 202, 'magli.enrico@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['DEEP LEARNING','DEEP LEARNING','VIDEO ANALYSIS','DEEP NEURAL NETWORKS','MACHINE LEARNING','MACHINE LEARNING','ARTIFICIAL NEURAL NETWORKS']::text[], 'APPLIED RESEARCH, RESEARCH', ARRAY['Ccne - Communications And Computer Networks Engineering','Ict4Ss - Ict For Smart Societies','Image Processing Lab (Ipl)']::text[], 'Available theses at Leonardo Labs
 Leonardo SpA is a provider of global security and advanced technology systems for applications in the aerospace, defense and security sectors. The company designs, develops, manufactures, and delivers helicopters, defense electronics and aerostructures. It also delivers satellites, orbiting manned infrastructures, apart from providing space related services such as earth observation from space, and satellite navigation and communication. 
 Leonardo has established the Leonardo Labs, an international network of corporate laboratories dedicated to advanced research and technological innovation (see link below). Within these labs, theses are available for M.Sc. students in the field of information and communication technologies, on the topics of satellite imaging and image processing/analysis. 
 Suitable candidates should have a GPA of 27/30 or higher. For more information, please contact enrico.magli@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['The candidate is required to have familiarity with neural networks and pytorch.']::text[], '', '2024-02-12', 2, ARRAY['LM-03 - Master Degree in Landscape Architecture']::text[]),
('Studio dei fattori di trascrizione in dati multi-omici single-cell, per la costruzione di legami enhancer-gene', 475, 'dicarlo.stefano@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Lorenzo Martini']::text[], ARRAY['BIOINFORMATICA','BIOLOGIA COMPUTAZIONALE','SINGLE-CELL DATA']::text[], 'RICERCA', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-24 - Smilies - Resilient Computer Architectures And Life Sci']::text[], 'L''obiettivo principale della tesi è di investigare il ruolo dei fattori di trascrizione nella regolazione dell''espressione genica a livello di singola cellula. In particolare, si vuole esplorare come i fattori di trascrizione interagiscono con gli enhancer e come questi legami influenzino l''espressione genica. Per raggiungere questo obiettivo, saranno utilizzati dati multi-omici single-cell, che includono informazioni sull''espressione genica, sull''accessibilità della cromatina. La tesi dovrà prima di tutto indagare gli strumenti e le tipologie di dati presenti in letteratura, per poi andare a definire una direzione di approccio al problema. In generale,  si andranno ad analizzare dati con tecniche di machine learning per poi creare modelli che investighino le correlazioni tra i vari elementi. I risultati di questa tesi potrebbero essere utilizzati per migliorare la comprensione della regolazione dell''espressione genica a livello di singola cellula e per identificare nuovi bersagli terapeutici per le malattie che coinvolgono la regolazione dell''espressione genica.
 Si richiede quindi molto impegno e volontà da parte del candidato, a provare una vera esperienza di ricerca in ambito bioinformatico.', ARRAY['Sono richieste conoscenze di base di machine learning, ed una preferibile conoscenza di R e/o Python.']::text[], '', '2024-04-21', 1, ARRAY['L-31 - Computer Science and Technologies','L-36 - Political Sciences and International Relations','L-10 - Letters']::text[]),
('Cost assessment of building sector technologies to comply with the targets of decarbonization strategies', 476, 'savoldi.laura@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['BUILDING ENERGY PERFORMANCE','ENERGY FORECAST','ENERGY MODELING','TIMES MODEL']::text[], 'RESEARCH, INNOVATIVE', ARRAY['Mahtep']::text[], 'The characterization of the residential and commercial sectors in the TEMOA-Italy and TEMOA Europe models dates back to the original outdated versions of TIMES-Italy and EUROfusion TIMES Model, respectively. However, the latest research advancements and policies make an update of those model sections necessary. In the perspective of studying new devoted scenarios (e.g., energy efficiency measures, energy storage applications) with a TEMOA instance, this thesis involves a renovation of the current techno-economic characterization of residential and commercial end-use technologies, to be included in an open-source database.', ARRAY['Attendance of the course "Models and scenarios for energy planning".']::text[], '', '2024-10-02', 2, ARRAY['LM-31 - Master Degree in Management Engineering','LM-16 - Master Degree in Finance']::text[]),
('Sviluppo di layer protettivi per batterie di nuova generazione litio-zolfo', 388, 'ginettenicoleamici.julia@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['francia.carlotta@tmtest.polito.it','versaci.daniele@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['BATTERIE','LITIO-ZOLFO','ALTA ENERGIA','SOSTENIBILITÀ']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE IN LABORATORIO', ARRAY['Aa - Elettrochemistry']::text[], 'La proposta di tesi rientra nel più ampio campo di ricerca dei materiali alternativi per post-litio ione e litio-zolfo e in particolar modo all’interno di progetti attivi all’interno del gruppo di ricerca.
 Il lavoro di tesi si pone l’obiettivo di sviluppare e caratterizzare dal punto di vista chimico-fisico ed elettrochimico layer attivi e selettivi in grado di incrementare le performance e la stabilità di batterie litio-zolfo (post litio-ione) di nuova generazione.
 L’attività sperimentale verrà svolta nei laboratori del gruppo di elettrochimica del dipartimento di Scienza Applicata e Tecnologia (DISAT).
 Le attività principali riguarderanno:
 - Preparazione delle formulazioni catodiche e preparazione degli elettrodi
 - Assemblaggio di celle e prototipi elettrochimici
 - Caratterizzazione elettrochimica delle celle/prototipi
 - Caratterizzazione chimico-strutturale dei materiali investigati
