('Studio della tecnologia e-pulse per avvitatori a pistola e angolari proposti da diversi fornitori con test in condizioni reali di utilizzo.', 418, 'mura.andrea@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['BIOMECCANICA','CARICO BIOMECCANICO','PRODUZIONE INDUSTRIALE']::text[], 'AZIENDALE', ARRAY['18-Progettazione E Sperimentazione Di Organi Di Trasmissione']::text[], 'L''obiettivo della tesi è valutazione della tecnologia e-pulse per avvitatori a pistola e angolari proposti da diversi fornitori con test in condizioni reali di utilizzo.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-06-14', 2, ARRAY['LM-31 - Master Degree in Management Engineering','LM-30 - Master Degree in Energy and Nuclear Engineering','LM-29 - Master Degree in Electronic Engineering']::text[]),
('Blockchain & smart vehicles: an onboard TBM wallet solution', 99, 'patti.edoardo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Davide Tonella (D.Tonella@Reply.It)']::text[], ARRAY['BLOCKCHAIN','ELECTRIC VEHICLE','SMART GRID','SMART VEHICLES']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Energy Center Lab','Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Ict4Ss - Ict For Smart Societies']::text[], 'The scope of the thesis is exploring the possibilities that the blockchain and tokenization technologies could bring to the world of smart grid and electric vehicles applications. 
The idea is to use the telematic box of connected vehicles to implement a wallet to allow the use of tokens on the blockchain, to be exchanged for energy from the power grid.
 The candidate will be required to:
1.	Study the state of the art regarding the usage of blockchain on board of EV
2.	Design and develop the onboard side of and end-to-end solution that implements the functionalities of a SW token wallet
3.	Integrate the SW on the telematic box (or similar HW) of a smart vehicle
4.	Cooperate with backend and blockchain domains experts, to ensure the flexibility, safety and reliability of the proposed solution
 The thesis will be supported by Concept Engineering Reply (https://www.reply.com/concept-reply), the company within the Reply Group specializing in digitizing and making the physical world smart through the development of IoT solutions applied to products, processes, and services. Concept Engineering relies on a group of experts in the fields of embedded systems (hardware and firmware), edge computing, IoT platforms, cloud computing, user channels, AI, ML, project management and PMO.
The target markets include automotive (and transportation in a broad sense), manufacturing, telco & media, insurance & finance, and medical. Additionally, an essential component of Concept Engineering is research and development, which aims to explore new technological frontiers to generate innovation.
Quality, innovation, flexibility, and enjoyment are the fundamental ingredients for making our projects successful and satisfying our clients.', ARRAY['C++, blockchain, MQTT or other communication protocol']::text[], '', '2024-10-24', 2, ARRAY['LM-04 - Master Degree in Architectural and Building Engineering-Architecture','LM-02 - Master Degree in Archaeology','LM-29 - Master Degree in Electronic Engineering']::text[]),
('Multi-fidelity modeling for design analysis and optimization: aerospace engineering applications', 455, 'maggiore.paolo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['mainini.laura@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['AEROSPACE DESIGN','MULTI-FIDELITY ANALYSIS','SURROGATE MODELING']::text[], 'NUMERICAL AND DESIGN ORIENTED', ARRAY['L-27 group 1']::text[], 'Students will be developing modeling strategies to combine and leverage information provided by different physical models; particular attention will be dedicated to numerical and experimental models representing physical systems at different level of fidelity, accuracy, and complexity. The research activities can be tailored on student’s interests upon discussion with the supervisors/PIs.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2023-12-31', 1, ARRAY['L-27 - Chemical Sciences and Technologies']::text[]),
