('Framework for performance evaluation of web-based and native networked music performance applications', 511, 'bianco.andrea@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['emmamargheritarottondi.cristina@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['NETWORKED MUSIC PERFORMANCE']::text[], 'SIMULATION/ANALYSIS', ARRAY['Telecommunication Networks Group']::text[], 'Networked music performance (NMP) enables remote musicians to perform together by means of low-latency audio/video streaming over a telecommunication network.
The objective of this thesis is to design an assessment framework to evaluate the performance and usability of various NMP solutions. The performance evaluation is carried out in terms of resources used, network bandwidth, audio quality (audio codec + packet loss concealment), mouth-to-ear latency and so on. The usability of the various tools instead will be carried out using a series of usability metrics. The project activities include initial research on the state-of-the-art tools which can be used for the various metric evaluations, followed by the development of a framework which can be used to quantitatively assess the performance of different NMP tools, which can be either web-application or native tools. In the last part of the thesis, the developed framework will be then used to evaluate the performance of various NMP tools.', ARRAY['Programming skills','previous experience with GNU/Linux']::text[], '', '2024-07-30', 1, ARRAY['L-10 - Letters']::text[]),
('Algoritmi avanzati di Natural Language Processing (es. ChatGPT) per la generazione automatica di contenuti', 371, 'aliberti.alessandro@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['patti.edoardo@tmtest.polito.it','Alessio Viticchié']::text[], ARRAY['MACHINE LEARNING','ARTIFICIAL NEURAL NETWORKS','NATURAL LANGUAGE PROCESSING']::text[], 'RICERCA APPLICATA', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Eda Group','Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Energy Center Lab','Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Ict4Ss - Ict For Smart Societies']::text[], 'Nell''ambito di un progetto di ricerca aziendale, lo studente investigherà lo stato dell''arte di tecniche di Natural Language Processing (NLP), con particolare attenzione al tool ChatGPT, per sviluppare e integrare funzionalità innovative per la generazione automatica di contenuti per gli utenti.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-01-11', 1, ARRAY['L-27 - Chemical Sciences and Technologies','L-38 - Zootechnical Sciences and Animal Production Technologies']::text[]),
('Relay switching fault detection through DSP and Artificial Intelligence techniques', 251, 'ruoroch.massimo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY[' the ']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Vlsilab (Vlsi Theory','Design And Applications)']::text[], 'A typical problem in high reliability relay based switching is the detection of contact stuck which can lead to impossibility to change relay state.
Detection through an auxiliary contact is sometimes possible, but it increases system cost.
This thesis aims to verify if ral time analysis of relay coil current, through either DSP algorithms, or through AI processing, is able to reliably detect contacts stuck.
Microcontroller and FPGA based solutions must be designed and implemented.', ARRAY['Micrcontrollers, Basic analog electronics, DSP, C-language, HDL']::text[], '', '2024-10-09', 1, ARRAY['L-31 - Computer Science and Technologies','L-05 - Philosophy','L-24 - Psychological Sciences and Techniques']::text[]),
('Acoustic optimization of robotic leg prosthesis chassis: innovative solutions to reduce human perceived noise', 54, 'shtrepi.louena@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY[' of ',' the ']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['LM-20 group 1','LM-03 group 1','LM-15 group 1']::text[], 'The project aims to investigate the possibility to reduce the emitted noise of lower limb robotic prostheses. The actuation unit is the main, inevitable noise source; thus, it is important to explore alternative solutions to tackle such issue. Specifically, the focus is towards the prosthesis chassis that has both a
structural and aesthetic meaning for the end user. Therefore, passive acoustic reduction techniques are more likely to succeed, given that weight and bulk are the other key ergonomic aspects for amputees. The project is framed within
