('Analisi e valutazione di performance ed autonomia di veicoli elettrici in esercizio nel trasporto pubblico ', 551, 'dallachiara.bruno@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['TRASPORTO PUBBLICO','TRAZIONE ELETTRICA']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['Trasporti']::text[], 'Analisi e valutazione di performance ed autonomia di veicoli elettici in esercizio nel trasporto pubblico', ARRAY['Materie di trasporti e possibilmente di motori elettrici']::text[], '', '2024-10-25', 2, ARRAY['LM-01 - Master Degree in Cultural Anthropology and Ethnology','LM-18 - Master Degree in Computer Science','LM-29 - Master Degree in Electronic Engineering']::text[]),
('Teleferiche: progettazione ed esercizio ', 551, 'dallachiara.bruno@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['IMPIANTI A FUNE']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['L-17 group 2','L-37 group 1']::text[], 'Teleferiche: progettazione ed esercizio', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-11-11', 1, ARRAY['L-17 - Architectural Sciences','L-37 - Social Sciences for Cooperation, Development, and Peace']::text[]),
('Reverse Engineering the Electromagnetic Circuitry of the Cell', 302, 'adamtuszynski.jacek@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['ACTIN FILAMENTS','CYTOSKELETON','ELECTRIC CIRCUITS','MEMBRANE CAPACITANCE','MICROTUBULES']::text[], 'COMPUTATIONAL', ARRAY['28- Biomedica']::text[], 'The objective of this project is to understand how electrical and electromagnetic stimuli affect the cell viewed as a bioelectric system. It is well known that cell membranes are “leaky” capacitors due to charge separation and ion currents flowing through ion channels. However, little is still known about the electrodynamic properties of the cytoskeleton. The cytoskeleton is a network of protein fibres in eukaryotic cells with microtubules (MTs) playing key roles in mitosis, motility, transport, structural integrity and signalling. Changes in MT organization are implicated in various pathologies, e.g. cancer and neurodegenerative disorders (NDDs). Recent experiments on the conductive and capacitive properteis of microtubules and actin filaments have provided us with reasonably accurate estimates of their electrical conduction parameters. Creating complex networks based on these structures will be a first step toward the analysis of the cytoskeleton as a dynamic RLC-circuit. We propose to investigate the key factors that affect the responses of the main elements of the cytoskeleton to electric and electromagnetic (EM) fields. Changes in the pH values, ion concentrations and structural organization of the filaments will be investigated in this respect. To characterize and quantify these processes, computational simulations of tubulin, the building block of MTs, as well as actin and actin filaments (AFs) will be performed. Major implications for human pathology and disease treatments will include mechanisms of cancer initiation and progression and causes of NDDs. Mechanisms of action of novel electric field-based therapies will be elucidated. Nanotechnological applications of this work are anticipated in the area of biosensors, bioelectronics and biological computing using MTs, AFs and their interconnections as EM-controllable signal processing units in complex circuits', ARRAY['understanding of electric circuits with R, C and L elements and their IV characteristics, familiarity with matlab or mathematica']::text[], '', '2024-03-02', 2, ARRAY['LM-21 - Master Degree in Biomedical Engineering','LM-08 - Master Degree in Industrial Biotechnology']::text[]),
('Data analytics techniques for monitoring the production quality of a tire extrusion machine', 159, 'vinco.sara@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Michele Ambrogio','Michelin']::text[], ARRAY['DATA ANALYTICS','INDUSTRY 4.0','MACHINE LEARNING','AI']::text[], 'MAGISTRALE', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda']::text[], 'La tesi prevede la costruzione di tecniche di data analytics per il monitoraggio di una macchina di estrusione (MX7),  prototipo assoluto nell’ambito dell’industria della gomma e soggetta a diversi brevetti Michelin, dedicata alla estrusione di battistrada. 
Il tesista dovrà studiare il processo e correlare i parametri prodotto processo di tale impianto con la geometria del prodotto ottenuto, al fine di monitorare e migliorare la qualità del prodotto stesso.
Necessità di collaborare con equipe locale e con tecnici della casa madre francese. Necessaria la conoscenza di almeno una lingua tra inglese, francese e tedesco (oltre all''italiano). 
Previsti 3 giorni full time/settimana presso Michelin Cuneo (località Ronchi). 
Previsto un rimborso spese. 

', ARRAY['Data analytics, programming']::text[], 'Vedi anche: moreinformation.pdf', '2023-11-30', 1, ARRAY['L-28 - Navigation Sciences and Technologies','L-15 - Tourism Sciences']::text[]),
('Preparazione di ionogel tramite fotopolimerizzazione come elettroliti innovativi per nuove generazioni di batterie al litio ', 388, 'ginettenicoleamici.julia@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['sangermano.marco@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['BATTERIE AL LITIO','ELETTROLITI','FOTOPOLIMERIZZAZIONDE']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Aa - Glasses','Ceramics And Composites']::text[], 'Preparazione di differenti formulazioni polimeriche reticolate tramite radiazione UV. Caratterizzazione fisico-chimica ed elettrochimica delle membrane ottenute.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-10-12', 1, ARRAY['L-11 - Modern Languages and Cultures']::text[]),
('Sicurezza Integrata per l''IoT: Metodologie e Certificazione per Dispositivi Smart Collaborativi', 402, 'ardito.luca@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Alessandro Aldini']::text[], ARRAY['CYBERSECURITY','IOT','MODEL CHECKING']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-16 - Software Engineering Group - Softeng']::text[], 'La proposta di tesi riguarda l''ambito dei dispositivi intelligenti IoT collaborativi e la necessità, in questo contesto, di meccanismi che certifichino l''integrazione conforme alla sicurezza tra API specifiche dei dispositivi e funzionalità generiche fornite da sviluppatori di applicazioni di terze parti. In particolare, scopo della tesi è progettare un insieme di meccanismi e metodologie da utilizzare come elementi costitutivi per supportare tale certificazione. Come applicazione pratica, sarà possibile testare l''approccio proposto su un prototipo proof-of-concept per un ambiente Smart Home. Le tecniche e gli approcci specifici riguardano il security-by-design, il controllo degli accessi e il policy enforcement, le tecniche di analisi della conformità basate su modelli, il model checking e, in generale, tecniche di verifica formale.', ARRAY['IoT, Sicurezza informatica, Security by Design, Analisi della conformità e Model Checking']::text[], '', '2024-11-04', 1, ARRAY['L-05 - Philosophy','L-02 - Biotechnology']::text[]),
('Music elaboration, models and algorithms', 171, 'guidomariosalassa.fabio@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY[' Formalizing these problems is crucial to enhance',' Goal',' performers and even for didactical purposes']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['L-16 group 2']::text[], 'Writing music requires solving several complex problems such as harmonization, pattern elaboration, fingering. Formalizing these problems is crucial to enhance the way on how music is generated and to propose support systems for composers, performers and even for didactical purposes. Goal of the thesis is to define models and provide solutions for some of these problems, providing examples and applications, using standard methods of Operations Research.
Coding skills in a programming language (for example: C++, Java or Python) and knowledge in the field of operations research are highly recommended as well as some experience on music notation.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-05-03', 1, ARRAY['L-16 - Administration and Organization Sciences']::text[]),
('Technical-economic assessment of technologies for EV battery management and state-of-health (SoH) prediction.', 453, 'bottaccioli.lorenzo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['patti.edoardo@tmtest.polito.it','Alessandro Perol (Edison Spa)']::text[], ARRAY['BATTERIE','BATTERY MANAGEMENT SYSTEM','ELECTRIC VEHICLE','SMART GRID','VEICOLI ELETTRIFICATI']::text[], 'AZIENDALE, RICERCA', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Energy Center Lab','Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda']::text[], 'The scope of the thesis is to study technological solutions available for EV battery management and state-of-health (SoH) prediction. The study starts from a comparative overview of the algorithms used and of the existing developers (at both university/start-ups and commercial level). This preliminary work will be essential to develop evaluation tools to analyze the real data gathered by a prototypal device, developed by a start-up, that Edison is testing on its electric vehicles. Data will be collected before and during the thesis period, both in specific tests at representative moments and in daily car drives. Creativity and data analysis skills will be required not only to prepare and analyze data, but also to propose integrations to data acquisition, when required to get the maximum value from the available set.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-03-17', 2, ARRAY['LM-10 - Master Degree in Conservation of Architectural and Environmental Heritage','LM-05 - Master Degree in Archival Studies and Library Science']::text[]),
('Data management and analysis for smart agriculture', 2, 'ferrero.renato@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['DATA ANALYTICS','DATA PROCESSING','INTERNET OF THINGS (IOT)','SENSOR NETWORKS']::text[], 'RESEARCH', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-05 - Electronic Cad & Reliability Group - Cad']::text[], 'Smart agriculture, also known as precision agriculture or digital farming, is an innovative approach that leverages advanced technologies and data-driven methodologies to enhance productivity, efficiency, and sustainability in agricultural practices. By integrating real-time monitoring and data analytics, smart agriculture enables informed decision-making and improved agricultural outcomes.
One of the key components of smart agriculture is the utilization of IoT devices and sensor technology, which enables the collection of real-time data from the field. In the thesis, the primary objective is to develop an IoT application capable of efficiently managing and processing the data gathered by these sensors. In particular, a basic requirement consists in the development of a comprehensive system for storing all the collected information in a shared database, while also facilitating continuous monitoring of the crops.
The second part of this thesis focuses on the analysis of the collected data. Specifically, the aim is to develop sophisticated analysis algorithms for sensor calibration and correlation pattern extraction. By analyzing the data, these algorithms will contribute to the accurate calibration of sensors, ensuring that the measurements obtained are reliable and precise. Furthermore, the algorithms will facilitate the extraction of meaningful patterns and correlations from the collected data, providing valuable insights into crop performance and environmental factors.', ARRAY['programming, relational database']::text[], '', '2024-06-06', 2, ARRAY['LM-03 - Master Degree in Landscape Architecture']::text[]),
('Food contamination monitoring via microwave imaging technology', 406, 'robertocasu.mario@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['savorani.francesco@tmtest.polito.it','vipiana.francesca@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['ANTENNA','MEASUREMENT','MODELING','COMPUTATIONAL ELECTROMAGNETICS','ALGORITHMS','FOOD INSPECTION','FPGA ACCELERATION','GPU','NVIDIA','ACCELERATOR','MICROWAVE DEVICES AND SYSTEMS','MICROWAVE IMAGING']::text[], 'TESI MAGISTRALE, TESI MULTIDISCIPLINARE, TESI SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['Applied Electromagnetics','Vlsi Theory','Design And Applications (Vlsilab)']::text[], 'Foreign body contamination in food is one of the major sources of complaints against food manufacturers, and can lead to injury, loss of brand loyalty and large recall expenses. Different technologies, such as X-ray or infrared techniques, are currently applied to detection systems used for food inspection, but physical contamination, with e.g. wood, plastic, metal and glass, is still present in food.
 The main objective of this Master Thesis is to investigate the use of the microwave imaging (MWI) technology for food contamination monitoring. MWI is able, through low-power electromagnetic (EM) waves at microwave frequencies, to non-invasively penetrate an object and provide a spatial map of its EM properties. Such a capability is herein relevant due to intrinsic difference in such properties between food and contaminants. 
 The main activities will be:
 - Characterization of the food/beverage dielectric properties: development of a data-base containing the dielectric properties, in the microwave frequency range, of common food and beverage;
 - Development of the imaging algorithms;
 - Antenna system design, prototyping and testing: the antenna system, to radiate the food/beverage products with the EM waves at microwave frequencies, will be designed and tested via full wave simulations together with the implemented imaging algorithms;
 - RF front-end back-end design and prototyping;
 - Accelerated implementation of the imaging algorithms with specialized hardware for inline monitoring (e.g. GPU, FPGA, …).
 During the Master Thesis the student(s) will work on one (or more) of the previous activities, related to the student background and interests.
 Main reference: J. A. Tobon Vasquez, R. Scapaticci, G. Turvani, M. Ricci, L. Farina, A. Litman, M. R. Casu, L. Crocco, F. Vipiana, “Non-invasive In-line Food Inspection via Microwave Imaging Technology”, IEEE Antennas and Propagation Magazine, Special issue on EM Imaging for Food, Vol. 62, No. 5, Oct. 2020, pp. 18-32, [DOI: 10.1109/MAP.2020.3012898]', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2023-12-03', 2, ARRAY['LM-24 - Master Degree in Building Systems Engineering','LM-11 - Master Degree in Conservation and Restoration of Cultural Heritage','LM-24 - Master Degree in Building Systems Engineering']::text[]),
