('Performance evaluation of satellite networks', 4, 'garello.roberto@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['giaccone.paolo@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['SATELLITE NETWORKS','SIMULATION','SPACE COMMUNICATIONS']::text[], 'GRAPH ALGORITHMS, OPTIMIZATION, SIMULATION', ARRAY['Telecommunication Networks Group']::text[], 'Satellite networks provides a novel communication paradigm by which satellite communicate and cooperate to send information across different sites on earth.
 The aim of the work is to consider the intermittent communication between satellite and evaluate the maximum performance (in terms of latency and bandwidth) by exploiting a store-carry-forward approach. A time-space graph model of the communication will be studied and a numerical solver will be developed to evaluate the performance for a large network of cooperative satellites.', ARRAY[]::text[], 'Communication systems. Python. Simulation models. Very good programming skills.', '2024-05-23', 1, ARRAY['L-35 - Mathematical Sciences']::text[]),
('Rilievo, analisi e proposte di recupero sostenibile di edifici storici in ambito alpino', 237, 'fasana.sara@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['osello.anna@tmtest.polito.it','zerbinatti.marco@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['PROGETTO','RESTAURO','DIAGNOSTICA','RECUPERO','SOSTENIBILITÀ DELLE COSTRUZIONI']::text[], 'PROGETTAZIONE', ARRAY['LM-27 group 2','LM-31 group 2']::text[], 'Sono proposti temi legati al recupero di edifici significativi per rilevanza storica, tecnologica, culturale e ambientale. I temi potranno essere sviluppati su edifici singoli, ovvero su complessi e tessuti edificati di valore riconosciuto; le proposte progettuali saranno indirizzate al riuso compatibile e sostenibile. Nei progetti, saranno considerati anche gli aspetti energetici e strutturali.', ARRAY['Tecniche di rilievo a scala di edificio e dei tessuti urbani (o di interesse ambientale), ottima cultura generale, ottima conoscenza dell''architettura tecnica in funzione del recupero, dei materiali e del loro comportamento in opera, delle nozioni fisico-tecniche di base.']::text[], '', '2024-03-12', 2, ARRAY['LM-27 - Master Degree in Telecommunications Engineering','LM-31 - Master Degree in Management Engineering']::text[]),
('Optimizing Lyophilization Efficiency through Advanced Nested Vial Design and Process Control', 138, 'pisano.roberto@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['FREEZE-DRYING','LIOFILIZZAZIONE','PRODUZIONE DI FARMACI','TRASFERIMENTO DI CALORE','TRASFERIMENTO DI MATERIA']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE, SPERIMENTALE E DI MODELLAZIONE', ARRAY['Aa - Mole (Molecular Engineering Lab)']::text[], 'This master''s thesis will explore the development and implementation of nested vials as a novel approach to enhance lyophilization efficiency in pharmaceutical manufacturing. The project will encompass both the design of specialized nested vials and the development of process control strategies to maximize product quality and yield during freeze-drying processes.', ARRAY[]::text[], 'The project activities will take place at the research laboratories of a leading vaccine production company located in Belgium. Alternatively, the project can be carried out in part or entirely in the Politecnico''s research laboratories.', '2024-09-08', 1, ARRAY['L-12 - Language Mediation']::text[]),
('Quantitative assessment of audio-induced vibrations on a metallic lamina for the generation of tactile feedback to ease music perception for blind, deaf and hard-of-hearing users ', 134, 'emmamargheritarottondi.cristina@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['DEAFBLINDNESS','HAPTIC DEVICES','MUSIC']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Telecommunication Networks Group']::text[], 'Enhancing inclusiveness in music fruition entails devising alternative sensory involvement for users with visual or auditory impairments. One possible option is the exploitation of tactile feedback, e.g., by means of vibrating surfaces that can help creating a more immersive experience for such categories of users. Though a number of studies exposing the benefits of the adoption of haptic feedback to ease music perception already exists, they almost always lack of technical details on the characteristics of the tactile stimuli offered to the users, thus hindering reproducibility and wide-scale adoption.
The goal of this thesis project is the quantitative assessment of the vibrations induced on a thin metallic lamina when hit by soundwaves generated by a loudspeaker reproducing audio signals, depending on the characteristics of the audio content being reproduced (e.g., timbre, pitch, tone, rhythm…) and on the loudspeaker technical specifications (e.g., traditional versus directional loudspeakers). The study will be complemented by test campaigns involving human subjects, to assess the discrimination capabilities among various types of vibrational stimuli. The thesis student will be co-tutored by Dr. Louena Shtrepi (DENERG, Politecnico di Torino).', ARRAY['knowledge of signal processing techniques and of theory of vibrations']::text[], '', '2024-08-25', 1, ARRAY['L-36 - Political Sciences and International Relations']::text[]),
