('Reconfigurable-oriented fault tolerance DSP applications for aerospace satellite electronic systems', 452, 'sterpone.luca@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['FPGA','SAFETY']::text[], 'RESEARCH', ARRAY['Dauin - Aerospace And Safety Computing Lab']::text[], 'The activity of the present thesis is oriented on the development of fault tolerance design techniques for satellite electronic system payload using the modern generation of Xilinx SRAM-based FPGAs that support dynamic reconfiguration (i.e., the possibility to change the physical design on-site and therefore correcting errors and optimizing performances). The activity of the thesis is executed in part in the CAD group of Politecnico di Torino, DAUIN and in part within the ESTEC laboratories of the European Space Agency (ESA) in Leiden, The Netherlands', ARRAY['Specification, Simulations of Digital Systems, VHDL, C/C++ languages']::text[], 'Fluent english', '2024-01-26', 2, ARRAY['LM-07 - Master Degree in Agricultural Biotechnology','LM-16 - Master Degree in Finance']::text[]),
