('Locally Distributed Real-Time Co-simulation Infrastructure applied to real Smart-Grid scenarios', 453, 'bottaccioli.lorenzo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['patti.edoardo@tmtest.polito.it','Abouzar Estebsari (Estebsaa@Lsbu.Ac.Uk)','Luca Barbierato (Luca.Barbierato@tmtest.polito.it)']::text[], ARRAY['CO-SIMULATION TECHNIQUES','DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS','HARDWARE IN THE LOOP','ICT','SMART CITY','MULTI-ENERGY-SYSTEM','NETWORKING','SIMULATION','SMART CITIES','SMART GRID','SMART GRIDS']::text[], 'SPERIMENTALE E DI MODELLAZIONE', ARRAY['Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Energy Center Lab','Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda','Ict4Ss - Ict For Smart Societies']::text[], 'One of the main objectives of the Energy Center LAB initiative consists on designing a Multi-Energy-System (MES) Co-Simulation Platform able to qualitatively and quantitatively solve energetic transition scenarios [1]. The co-simulation infrastructure of Energy Center Lab will integrate different Digital Real-time Simulator (DRTS), such as RTDS Technologies and OpalRT, that provides power systems simulation technology for fast, reliable, accurate and cost-effective study of power systems. DRTS permits also to interconnect real hardware components to test their functionalities in simulated complex smart grid scenarios. This co-simulation approach is called Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL). The aims of the thesis consist on:
1.	State of the Art analysis of the Power HIL (PHIL) Interface Algorithm (IA)
2.	Implement a frequency stability analysis of different PHIL IA from a control system engineering perspective
3.	Familiarize with two different DRTS commercial solution: OpalRT and RTDS Technology
4.	Familiarize with the two software that control the commercial DRTS: RT-LAB and RSCAD
5.	Familiarize with the Energy Center LAB Local Distributed Real-Time Co-simulation Infrastructure and its main technology pillars
6.	Propose a Smart Grid scenario that will be run in standalone on both DRTS, and in a co-simulative environment by splitting it in two DRTS
7.	Assess the time-domain accuracy and frequency-domain accuracy of the co-simulated Smart Grid scenario with respect to the standalone result
8.	Propose a newer PHIL IA to reduce the effect of the non-linearities generated by the interconnection of the DRTS in the Energy Center LAB Local Distributed Real-Time Co-simulation Infrastructure
 [1] P. Mancarella. MES (Multi-Energy Systems): An overview of concepts and evaluation models. Energy, 65:1–17, 2014.', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2024-10-14', 2, ARRAY['LM-09 - Master Degree in Medical, Veterinary, and Pharmaceutical Biotechnology','LM-07 - Master Degree in Agricultural Biotechnology','LM-28 - Master Degree in Electrical Engineering']::text[]),
('Simulatore del livello 0 per il radar Doppler della missione ESA Earth Explorer 11 WIVERN', 31, 'battaglia.alessandro@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['maggiora.riccardo@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['DOPPLER','RADAR','RADARMETEOROLOGIA','SIGNAL PROCESSING','SIMULAZIONE','TELERILEVAMENTO','VENTO']::text[], 'NUMERICA E PROGETTUALE', ARRAY['Telerilevamento Di Nubi E Precipitazioni']::text[], 'La missione WIVERN (WInd VElocity Radar Nephoscope, www.wivern.polito.it), incentrata su un radar Doppler a 94 GHz con scanning conico per la misura dei venti orizzontali, e'' stata selezionata per intraprendere studi di fase 0 nel programma degli Earth Explorer dell''ESA. Il radar che verrà operato con scanning conico, misurerà le componenti sulla linea di vista del vento su una swath larga 800 km. Scopo della tesi è sviluppare un simulatore per le misure di livello 0 (I and Q del segnale radar) a partire da scene atmosferiche tri-dimensionali con assegnato spettro Doppler.', ARRAY['Eccellente livello di programmazione in Matlab/python. 
