('Non-linear identification of structures and hybrid simulations', 102, 'ceravolo.rosario@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Gaetano Miraglia (Eed Lab','R3C)','Giuseppe Abbiati (Assistant Professor At University Of Aarhus','Eed Lab)']::text[], ARRAY['EARTHQUAKE ENGINEERING']::text[], 'EXPERIMENTAL AND SIMULATIONS', ARRAY['Computational Methods In Civil Engineering','University Of Aarhus (Dk)','Earthquake Engineering & Dynamics Lab']::text[], 'Increase the efficiency of probabilistic updating of non-linear dynamic systems subjected to stochastic seismic excitation, toreduce the computational requirements without affecting accuracy. Tools:  non-linear autoregressive models; surrogate models. Application: hybrid simulation and testing of structures (coupling physical and mathematical models)', ARRAY['Matlab']::text[], '', '2024-10-30', 1, ARRAY['L-34 - Geological Sciences','L-30 - Physical Sciences and Technologies']::text[]),
('Analisi di processi di recupero e riciclaggio di celle a ossidi solidi', 152, 'fiore.silvia@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['luciafiorilli.sonia@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['BATTERY','CIRCULAR ECONOMY','ENERGY STORAGE','RECYCLING']::text[], 'BIBLIOGRAFICA + SVILUPPO, RICERCA APPLICATA, SPERIMENTALE', ARRAY['L-31 group 1']::text[], 'studio sperimentale del recupero di materie prime critiche e secondarie da celle a ossidi solidi', ARRAY[]::text[], '', '2023-11-28', 1, ARRAY['L-31 - Computer Science and Technologies']::text[]),
('Self/weakly-supervised learning to improve Renal Cancer subtyping', 432, 'dicataldo.santa@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['Francesco.Ponzio@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['IMAGE ANALYSIS','MACHINE LEARNING','ARTIFICIAL NEURAL NETWORKS','MEDICAL IMAGING','SELF-SUPERVISED LEARNING']::text[], 'Tesi all''estero', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-06 - Electronic Design Automation - Eda']::text[], 'Renal cell carcinoma (RCC) is currently categorized into several main histological subtypes. Importantly, the outcome of RCC malignant neoplasms deeply relies on the accurate determination of the histological subtype. Although histological diagnosis of renal neoplasm is usually straightforward by routine light microscopy, the categorization of histological RCC subtypes typically shows a poor to fair agreement between pathologists, with a mean inter-observer value in the range 0.32– 0.55. 
The aim of the thesis activity is to design and to validate a self/weakly-supervised learning-based system able to automatically classify tissue samples (in form of histological slides) into four RCC subtypes: clear cell RCC (ccRCC), papillary RCC (pRCC), chromophobe RCC (chRCC), and renal oncocytoma (ONCO). 
The thesis period is abroad at the research center Inria Sophia Antipolis - Méditerranée.', ARRAY['Good programming skills (Python). Prior experience with machine learning/deep learning design frameworks is a plus.']::text[], '', '2024-07-28', 2, ARRAY['LM-16 - Master Degree in Finance']::text[]),
('Network emulation with programmable switches and smart NICs in 5G/6G networks', 511, 'bianco.andrea@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['giaccone.paolo@tmtest.polito.it']::text[], ARRAY['PROGRAMMABLE DATA PLANES','P4']::text[], 'EXPERIMENTAL / DEVELOPMENT', ARRAY['Telecommunication Networks Group']::text[], 'Network emulation is a fundamental tool to test performance of applications running on virtualized environments (e.g., Docker containers, virtual machines), as in a typical 5G/6G scenario. Traditional solutions are based on server-managed traffic control schemes, which are very flexible (e.g., tc netem in Linux) but have limited capability in terms of bandwidth and latency.
In the last few years, programmable data plane devices as P4 swithes and smart NICs (e.g., NVidia Bluefield)  have been offering very high performance processing, but with different level of flexibility.
 Aim of the thesis will be to investigate how to use a programmable data plane to emulate a network.', ARRAY['Linux 
