('Floating offshore solar photovoltaic systems: modelling and techno-economic assessment', 366, 'giorgi.giuseppe@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['FLOATING SOLAR PV','FOTOVOLTAICO','RENEWABLE ENERGY','SOLARE']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['LM-28 group 1']::text[], 'Solar Photovoltaic (PV) has become one of the cheapest technology to produce renewable energy. However, among the challenges to a pervasive implementation there are the use of land, subtracted to
other stakeholders. Floating PV systems are an interesting alternative, with additional benefits of water cooling and higher efficiency. While already advanced for small enclosed water basins, more innovative ambitious applications are offshore at sea. 
