('Tidal energy converters: modelling and techno-economic assessment', 366, 'giorgi.giuseppe@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['C.Windt@Tu-Braunschweig.De']::text[], ARRAY['RENEWABLE ENERGY','TIDAL ENERGY']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['LM-15 group 1','LM-11 group 2','LM-20 group 2']::text[], 'Tidal energy is one of the most predictable sources of renewable energy, since it is related to astronomical cycles. Moreover, tidal energy turbines are among the most mature ocean energy technologies. However, the decision-making process necessitates of comparable techno-economic metrics, hence not only productivity, but also capital and operational costs. 
