('An effective environment to generate test programs for pipelined processors resorting to formal techniques', 178, 'cantoro.riccardo@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['sonzareorda.matteo@tmtest.polito.it','Nikolaos Deligiannis']::text[], ARRAY['FORMAL TECHNIQUES','FUNCTIONAL TEST','PIPELINED PROCESSORS','SAT SOLVERS']::text[], 'Tesi di Laurea', ARRAY['Dauin - Gr-05 - Electronic Cad & Reliability Group - Cad']::text[], 'Formal techniques are a promising approach able to face problems corresponding to the identification of a possible set of input values able to satisfy a given property by a Boolean formula. Many engineering problems can be represented as a set of Boolean expressions, and formal techniques can be used to effectively solve them. In the recent past, some advancements in the state-of-the-art of these techniques, and the availability of more powerful computing systems allowed formal techniques to be used for the solutions of some interesting problems on pipelined processors, such as generating a test program able to detect a fault in the CPU hardware, or maximize the switching activity in a given module of the CPU. The CAD Group working in the Dept. of Control and Computer Engineering works from several years on these topics in cooperation with the University of Friburg in Germany. 
Students working on this project will use the FriTest environment developed by the University of Friburg, allowing the user to exploit the power of a state-of-the-art SAT solver for solving problems related to processors. Their task will be to
1) customize the environment so that it can effectively work on a RISC-V processor, facing one of the above problems (i.e., generating a program able to detect a fault, maximizing the Switching Activity in a CPU module, identifying safe faults) 
2) run experiments aiming at understanding the advantages and limitations of the environment
3) develop optimized solutions able to widen the capabilities of the environment.', ARRAY['This proposal is suitable for students enrolled in Computer Engineering. Students from other other curricula will be evaluated case by case.']::text[], '', '2024-01-16', 1, ARRAY['L-41 - Statistics','L-19 - Education and Training Sciences']::text[]),
('Analisi numerica per lo studio idrologico di acquiferi carsici', 449, 'butera.ilaria@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY['vigna.bartolomeo@tmtest.polito.it','Prof. Stefano Ferraris','Dott. Ing. Alessandro Pansa']::text[], ARRAY['portata circolante negli acquiferi mediante modellazione numerica','sutdio riguardano acquiferi del Piemonte meridionale']::text[], 'NUMERICA', ARRAY['LM-23 group 1','LM-12 group 1']::text[], 'La tesi proposta vuole identificare il modello che lega piogge e neve alla portata circolante negli acquiferi mediante modellazione numerica. I casi di sutdio riguardano acquiferi del Piemonte meridionale.', ARRAY['matlab']::text[], '', '2024-07-29', 2, ARRAY['LM-23 - Master Degree in Civil Engineering','LM-12 - Master Degree in Design']::text[]),
('Modellazione CAD di component in materiale composito per  applicazioni automotive', 324, 'mariacura.francesca@tmtest.polito.it', ARRAY[]::text[], ARRAY['MODELLAZIONE 3D','MATERIALI COMPOSITI']::text[], 'SIMULATIVA E PROGETTUALE', ARRAY['18-Progettazione E Sperimentazione Di Organi Di Trasmissione']::text[], 'La tesi prevede l’acquisizione di alcuni tra gli strumenti più
